 Port Elizabeth - The Anti-Gang Unit arrested a 28-year-old suspect wanted in an attempted murder, which allegedly took place on 1 February 2019. "It is alleged that at about 20:30, the victim, aged 29, and his friends were walking in Capulet Street in Booysens Park when an unknown person approached them and fired several shots at them," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "The victim sustained gunshot wounds to the head, left upper leg and left thigh and was taken to hospital for medical treatment." On Tuesday, at about 08:50, the suspect was arrested at a house in Steenbras Street in Booysens Park. "He is expected to appear in court soon." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 